          "The cotton gin and King Cotton — Eli Whitney's invention was meant to reduce the need for slave labor; it did the opposite. Cotton grew vastly more profitable, planters demanded more land and more enslaved people to work it, and the Deep South and the domestic slave trade expanded. A machine meant to ease labor deepened bondage instead.",
