        notebooking: "NB Page 5 (The Battle of the Ironclads), NB Page 6 (The 54th Massachusetts at Fort Wagner), or NB Page 7 (Surrender at Appomattox). Illustrate the scene. Caption: one sentence — what is happening and why does it matter?",
        civicsLinks: ["Q.92 — Name the U.S. war between the North and the South (the Civil War)", "Q.93 — The Civil War had many important events. Name one", "Q.94 — Abraham Lincoln is famous for many things. Name one", "Q.95 — What did the Emancipation Proclamation do?", "Q.96 — What U.S. war ended slavery? (the Civil War)"],
        watchFor: "Be precise about the Emancipation Proclamation: it freed enslaved people in the Confederate states then in rebellion — where Lincoln had no immediate power to enforce it — and did not free those in the loyal border states. This was careful war strategy, not contradiction; abolishing slavery everywhere required the 13th Amendment. Frame the 54th Massachusetts correctly: these men fought for their own freedom, not merely for others. Tell the assassination quietly, and let Lincoln's Second Inaugural close the war: 'With malice toward none, with charity for all... let us bind up the nation's wounds.'",
